songs.full_title: Cars with the Boom by L'Trimm
songs.title: Cars with the Boom

description.plain:
With “Cars with the Boom”, short-lived 1980s Miami rap duo L'Trimm, consisting of Tigra (later Lady Tigra) and Bunny D, wrote a perfect ode to the cars of Miami, but not just any cars: they’re talking about cars with speakers loud enough to make it sound like a “boom” when you play music.

The single is arguably their best known song and unarguably their highest-charting song, and it’s considered a significant part of Miami bass — a hip-hop subgenre defined by 808s, “hissing” cymbals, record scratching, and heavy bass — as a movement.

“Cars with the Boom” was named one of the 10 most essential Miami bass songs by Mixmag and the 10th best Miami rap song by Complex. It’s also considered a monumental hip-hop song in general, with VH1 and Rolling Stone ranking it the 95th and 100th greatest hip-hop song of all time, respectively.

The song regained a surge in popularity after becoming a part of multiple TikTok trends beginning in early May 2020.
